EDITOR APPROVED

You are wondering what is this 'Editor Approved'?

Well, this is pretty awesome! In order for the post to qualify and receive this accolade, it has to have a minimum of 700 words and two images (at least one original).

Receiving this accolade means two things: 1) Your content is amazing! Good job! 2) Your content qualifies for our monetization program. Every week two of the most read posts receive monetary rewards.

Christmas Decor on a Budget: Under $100

149 views
  • by Erica Sullivan 8 followers
FOLLOW WHATTHECLIQUE

    I love decorating for the holidays as much as the next girl, but the reality is I’m a senior in college and saving every penny to move in the spring. I don’t have the budget (or sadly space) to buy and store a ton of decorations. If you’re also taking the minimalistic approach to the holidays, you’ve come to the right place! I’ve rounded up the best decorations under $100, so we don’t have to miss out on the holiday cheer! Want more holiday decor on a budget? Visit my Amazon shop page! 

    Oh, Christmas Tree! 

    There is nothing better than a real Christmas tree that warms the house with scents of pine, spruce or fir. Unfortunately, getting a real tree isn't feasible for everyone. Because I live in a college apartment, I have a 5-foot artificial tree that hiding in my hall close until November. 


                 


    Let's Eat!

    Besides a decorated Christmas tree, a decorated table is my second favorite way to start the holiday season. My mom kills it when it comes to holiday tablescapes in terms of creativity. For this reason, it has always been something I look forward to on Thanksgiving and Christmas.

               

    The Best Way to Spread Christmas Cheer... 

    If you can’t finish this famous Christmas saying, you need to stop whatever you’re doing and watch ELF. But in all honesty, what’s a tree without decorations? I’ve rounded up some fun items from faux fur tree skirts to affordable Christmas lights that will give your tree something a little extra this holiday season.
